    "text": "<span style=\"color: rgb(58, 58, 58); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);\">Narbondel is the only unshaped piece of stone within the boundaries of the city cavern, and it is used as a clock. At the end of every day, the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Archmage_of_Menzoberranzan\" title=\"Archmage of Menzoberranzan\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: initial; color: var(--theme-link-color--hover); transition: color 0.3s; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);\">Archmage of Menzoberranzan</a><span style=\"color: rgb(58, 58, 58); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);\">&nbsp;casts magic upon the stone to heat it. The heat from the Archmage's spell forms a band around it and moved up. When the end of the glow was at the pillar's top, the day is almost done.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(58, 58, 58); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248); font-size: 10px; text-wrap-mode: nowrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(58, 58, 58); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);\">When the pillar is completely dark, it is called \"Narbondel's Black Death\" (effectively midnight).</span> ",
    "tooltip": "Narbondel, <i>the stalagmate clock </i>",
